description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit enthusiastic Health Care Assistant&#39;s to join the Paediatric Complex Care Team. We provide high quality care to enable children and young people with complex health needs and technology dependency to live with support in their own home. The successful applicant should be able to demonstrate a willingness and commitment to team working, have experience of working with children and families and have great communication skills. Level 2 NVQ in health and social care is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position involves shift work covering days, nights and weekends in children’s own homes. Our office is based in Congleton but the care packages are across the whole of East Cheshire, therefore travel is an essential part of this role, please demonstrate on your application form how you would meet this requirement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is a Permanent Post for 22.5 and 30 hours per week and a Fixed Term for 6 months post for 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 22.5, 30, 37.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced with Barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Jane Kinealy Job title Complex Care Team Leader Email address jane.kinealy@nhs.net Telephone number 07824481772&lt;/p&gt;
